The paper proposes a new selection rule for coordinate descent methods for optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed scheme, which involves numerical computations, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) another likely category. Additionally, the paper presents numerical experiments with Lasso and Ridge regression, which are common techniques in data science, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible category. The paper also discusses optimization and efficiency, which are topics covered in cs.Opt (Optimization) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
